CF HB 399
By: Senator Lewis Young (Chair, Joint Committee on Pensions)
Introduced and read first time: January 23, 2026
Assigned to: Budget and Taxation
Committee Report: Favorable
Senate action: Adopted
Read second time: February 19, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 State Retirement and Pension System – Transfers Between Systems –
3 Workgroup – Extension
4 FOR the purpose of extending the reporting date and the termination date for a workgroup
5 convened by the State Retirement Agency to study transfers of member service
6 between State and local retirement and pension systems; altering the entities to
7 which the State Retirement Agency is required to report; and generally relating to
8 transfers of member service between State and local retirement and pension
9 systems.
10 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
11 Chapter 768 of the Acts of the General Assembly of 2025
12 Section 1(a)(1)
13 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
14 Chapter 768 of the Acts of the General Assembly of 2025
15 Section 1(d) and 2
16 BY repealing and reenacting, without amendments,
17 Chapter 769 of the Acts of the General Assembly of 2025
18 Section 1(a)(1)
19 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
20 Chapter 769 of the Acts of the General Assembly of 2025
21 Section 1(d) and 2
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
Underlining indicates amendments to bill.
Strike out indicates matter stricken from the bill by amendment or deleted from the law by
amendment. *sb0338*

2 SENATE BILL 338
1 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
2 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
3 Chapter 768 of the Acts of 2025
4 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
5 That:
6 (a) (1) The State Retirement Agency shall convene a workgroup of interested
7 stakeholders to study the requirements and processes for transfers of member service
8 between State and local retirement and pension systems and make recommendations to
9 improve the process of transfers between systems.
10 (d) On or before [December 1, 2025] OCTOBER 1, 2026, the State Retirement
11 Agency shall submit a report of the findings and recommendations of the workgroup,
12 including the need for any legislative initiatives, to the Governor and, in accordance with §
13 2–1257 of the State Government Article, the [General Assembly] SENATE BUDGET AND
14 TAXATION COMMITTEE, THE HOUSE APPROPRIATIONS COMMITTEE, AND THE
15 JOINT COMMITTEE ON PENSIONS.
16 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect June
17 1, 2025. It shall remain effective for a period of [1 year] 2 YEARS and 1 month and, at the
18 end of June 30, [2026] 2027, this Act, with no further action required by the General
19 Assembly, shall be abrogated and of no further force and effect.
20 Chapter 769 of the Acts of 2025
21 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
22 That:
23 (a) (1) The State Retirement Agency shall convene a workgroup of interested
24 stakeholders to study the requirements and processes for transfers of member service
25 between State and local retirement and pension systems and make recommendations to
26 improve the process of transfers between systems.
27 (d) On or before [December 1, 2025] OCTOBER 1, 2026, the State Retirement
28 Agency shall submit a report of the findings and recommendations of the workgroup,
29 including the need for any legislative initiatives, to the Governor and, in accordance with §
30 2–1257 of the State Government Article, the [General Assembly] SENATE BUDGET AND
31 TAXATION COMMITTEE, THE HOUSE APPROPRIATIONS COMMITTEE, AND THE
32 JOINT COMMITTEE ON PENSIONS.
33 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect June
34 1, 2025. It shall remain effective for a period of [1 year] 2 YEARS and 1 month and, at the

